ce:section.ce:para:
The developed ENR sensing system was applied to determine tap water and river water samples to verify its feasibility. Under the above optimal conditions, ENR in all the water samples spiked with different concentrations of ENR (2, 8 and 13 μg·mL−1) was determined to calculate the recoveries (summarized in Table 1
                        ). It was found that the recoveries of ENR are within the range of 96.5%–109% with an RSD changed from 1.5% to 2.3%. Besides, some reported methods for ENR detection were also summarized in Table 2
                        . The present ENR sensing system has not only a wide detection range, but also a low LOD. In addition, the analysis procedure has been proved to be simple, convenient and low cost compared to other methods.
